						We minimize callbacks, we maximize quality
					

						We take our customers satisfaction very seriously. 
					






						Crafting designs to take you there
					

						Tell us your idea. We will make it happen.
					






						We identify and balance structural requirements with stunning design and function.
					

						Professional installations with certificated INSTALLATION MASTERS technicians.
					










					US Glass & Glazing, LLC began in 1990 as Barrett Contracting, Inc. (BCI), a family owned custom millwork business.
				



					In 1993  Andersen Window Corporation contracted BCI to provide warranty and repair from Key West to Biloxi.  The BCI team of accredited installers became certified with Andersen, Pella, Marvin, Peachtree, Zeluck, Tishler, MQ, EFCO, WinDoor, PGT, Euro-Wall and CWS windows and doors. 
				



					BCI has worked closely with leading Architects, Engineers and Manufacturers successfully designing fenestration details using the "whole building concept". 
				





					About US Glass
				

					BCI changed it's corporate name to US Glass & Glazing, LLC in December of 2013 and became a State Certified General Contractor (CGC1517830).  
				



					Mr. Barrett is a Nationally Certified Instructor and trade member of the American Architectural Manufacturers Association (AAMA) and INSTALLATION MASTERS.  Services include professional window and door installation, storefront and curtain wall installation, Thermal Imaging, ASTM 1103 Chamber Testing, Certified Engineering for Building Design Pressure, Consulting and Project Management.  Licensed and insured.
				












TESTIMONIALS










Amelia Island Condos


Oceans Three Condos


Flagler College


Peninsula Condos


Sea Dunes Condos


Lee Wasilewski





								Amelia Island Condos
							

								I would like to thank you and your firm for your professional assistance in completing our construction project. This project was a major undertaking involving repairs resulting from water intrusion in 230 units, removal and replacement of almost 2000 windows and replacing flashing and moisture protection around all apertures in 19 buildings. With your help as the primary contractor for most of the work, we were able to complete the work within a reasonable schedule, on budget, and with a minimum of problems. Your team did professional work, kept the premises accessible to the residents, kept the property free from construction debris and worked well with residents as well as the project team.
							

								In a day where overruns, sloppy work, poor service and conflict seem to be the norm, our experience was refreshingly free of those things. Once again, thank you for your help.
							
	
							V. Roach, Treasurer.
							



								Oceans Three Condos
							

								After all the time and troubles, I am told by my Aunt Marilyn that she loves the window. I understand that sometimes things just don't always work smoothly no matter how hard you try, but the end result is what matters the most. She also had high praise for your crew (crews) that made the difficult installation without inconveniencing her a lot. I look forward to seeing it myself soon.
							

								D. Fetner
							



								Ponce de Leon Building - Flagler College
							

								This is just a note to thank you for your continued efforts on our projects together. Over the past three years, we've installed somewhere in the neighborhood of 300 windows in the historic Ponce de Leon building at Flagler College. Your team of installers has been able to work in a historic structure and complete each project on schedule. I look forward to the next project with your firm.
							

								F. Rounsaville
							



								 Peninsula Condos
							

								My husband went to South Florida yesterday and decided to stop in Daytona this afternoon to see the windows. He is at our unit tonight. He called me and couldn't be happier with all the new doors and windows! He said in the master bedroom you could not hear any traffic noise anymore. He said it's very windy right now and in the living room....no sound! But when you go in the guest bedroom ocean side where you haven't gotten the new one in yet, he said you could hear a lot of wind noise.
	

The doors were amazing to him with their ease of use. He commented on how professional and neat everything your construction areas are. He called to thank me for doing the homework in selecting these windows and your company. So, I thought I would pass along the compliment, which actually goes to you!
							

								V. Hewatt
							



								Sea Dunes Condos
							

								Your company has done an excellent, diligent and conscientious job of correcting poor installation techniques and replacing various incompatible materials that have been used on our building.
							

								Jerry Seneker
							



								 This window has changed my life
							




Lee Wasilewski enjoying his balcony thanks to a accessible wheelchair window at Dimucci Twin Towers, Daytona Beach, Florida.
							





























